             confirmed the finding the Goods in the Prisoner's Bed as aforesaid, Mr.Jones confirmed, the same, and farther deposed, that the Prisoner when he took him denied that he broke open the Door, saying that he went in at the Cellar Door, having taken away the Key of it beforehand; and in expectation of Favour told them where he had pawn'd the other piece of Tiking to a poor Woman, which they found accordingly. 
               <persName id="t17201207-14-person86">
