             deposed, that the Prisoner brought a piece of Tiking to her, and desired her to pawn in for 30 s. for him, but the Broker would lend no more than 15 s. which he consented to take; but she being unwilling to go back again and having sav'd up so much to buy her Husband a Frock, let the Prisoner have it upon the Tiking. The Prisoner denied the stealing the Goods, and said that a Man brought them to him. <rs id="t17201207-14-verdict74" type="verdictDescription">
